                            <comment id="66795" author="jlevi" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2013 22:35:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3962&quot; title=&quot;Fix horrible file names in standard path&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3962&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3962&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64683" author="morrone" created="Tue, 20 Aug 2013 23:01:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we&apos;ll need to make that call on a case by case basis.  config.sh doesn&apos;t sound like something that should be in a user&apos;s standard PATH.  Sounds like a config file that should be located somewhere else.  Some of the others might just need a rename.  Or perhaps should not be part of the main lustre package.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64407" author="mdiep" created="Fri, 16 Aug 2013 15:55:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Chris, I want to make sure I understand before proceed. Should we rename these files to a more appropriate name or move to other directory/path. - thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64273" author="morrone" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 19:05:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, thank you, I think that is a good list.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
